news.title: Infibeam Avenues acquires Sintex Group's commercial tower in Ahmedabad for Rs 90 crore
news.para: In March, Reliance Industries completed its Rs 3,567-crore acquisition of Sintex Industries, exactly a year after banks had approved the acquisition and a month after the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) approved the transaction.

news.title: ED plans to seek review of SC bail to M3M promoters
news.para: The apex court had allowed bail to the promoters of M3M Group on their plea that they had been called by the agency for questioning in a money laundering case related to Ireo real estate developers.

news.title: Punjab & Haryana HC grants bail to M3M group MD in money laundering case
news.para: The high court also made it clear that once the arrest itself is held to be illegal, all other subsequent actions would be of no consequence and would have to fail.

news.title: MCD changes building plan sanction fee, houses to cost more in east & south Delhi
news.para: Officials said the fee was so far levied in the areas under the erstwhile north corporation, and since the unification of the three civic bodies, there was a constant demand for its implementation across the MCD jurisdiction.

news.title: Telangana builders seek revision in RERA Act & state portal
news.para: Sunil Chandra Reddy, president of Naredco Telangana, on Wednesday requested the central government to consider reduction of the penalty to 5% from 10% if the project is not registered under RERA.

news.title: S&P says WeWork is in 'selective default'
news.para: S&P's statement came a day after WeWork recounted its latest communications with creditors, saying in a securities filing that bond holders had given it a 30-day grace period on October 2 on interest payments.

news.title: LIC Housing Finance posts net profit of Rs 1,191.86 crore in Q2 FY24
news.para: The board of directors has approved the upfront commitment of Rs 150 crore to the corpus fund-LICHFL Real Estate Debt Opportunities Fund-1 of LICHFL Asset Management Company.

news.title: Kansai Nerolac Paints' net profit up 57.79% in Q2 FY24
news.para: Kansai Nerolac Paints' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,978.56 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 2.25 per cent from Rs 1,935.03 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: US jury finds National Association of Realtors liable for inflating commissions, awards $1.78 billion damages
news.para: The verdict by a federal jury in Kansas City, Missouri, could upend decades-old practices that have allowed real estate agents to boost commissions as home prices and mortgage rates rise, hurting consumers by making housing transactions more expensive.

news.title: Can't set riders on PAP rehabilitation land: Bombay HC nixes order cancelling Solapur allotment
news.para: A 2,500-sqft plot was allotted to a PAP in 1976. Almost four decades later, a complaint was filed alleging non-compliance of the allotment condition, which was to construct a house within a year. The state cancelled the allotment.

news.title: Ajmera Realty's net profit dips 34.08% in Q2 FY24
news.para: Ajmera Realty's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 147.59 crore in Q2 FY24, a dip of 21.13 per cent from Rs 187.14 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Nagpur metro phase-II land acquisition to pick speed
news.para: The meeting comes in the backdrop of several pending proposals for land acquisitions in Metro project. The collector instructed the revenue department to dispose of all land acquisition proposals immediately.

news.title: Cera Sanitaryware's net profit grows 12.24% in Q2 FY24
news.para: Cera Sanitaryware's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 476.23 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 11.66 per cent from Rs 426.51 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Trichy: 14.1 acre allocated for Tidel Park
news.para: The previous allotment of 8.9 acres of land was cancelled as the Tidel management sought a larger land parcel to construct a mega office space for IT and ITES companies near the upcoming integrated bus terminus (IBT).

news.title: Arvind SmartSpaces posts net profit of Rs 10.83 crore in Q2 FY24
news.para: Arvind SmartSpaces' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 75.27 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 45.82 per cent from Rs 51.62 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Haryana first state in country to implement property ID: Minister
news.para: Prime Minister Narendra Modi commended Chief Minister Manohar Lal Khattar for the ‘Creation of New Property-ID under Normal and Tatkaal Scheme’ and recommended other states to adopt it.

news.title: Ambuja Cements posts net profit of Rs 987.24 crore in Q2 FY24
news.para: The company's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 7,899.99 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 9.11 per cent from Rs 7,240.69 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Housing policy draft to be cleared in December: Maharashtra housing minister
news.para: The policy is expected to lay focus on skilled manpower, rental housing schemes for migrant workers and colonies for senior citizens. Besides, it will also include sops for affordable housing and measures for quick approvals, the minister said.

news.title: India Cements posts net loss of Rs 85.54 crore in Q2 FY24
news.para: The India Cements' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,272.41 crore in Q2 FY24, a dip of 4.88 per cent from Rs 1,337.70 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.
